  "id": "php/createarrays",
  "contentHtml": "<h1>Create Array</h1>\n<p>Use the array() function.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Or use [] brackets.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\">&#x3C;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span> = <span class=\"hljs-keyword\">array</span>(<span class=\"hljs-string\">'Tomato'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">'Apple'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">'Banana'</span>);\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span> = [<span class=\"hljs-string\">'Tomato'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">'Apple'</span>, <span class=\"hljs-string\">'Banana'</span>];\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\">?></span>\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Multiple lines</h2>\n<p>Line breaks do not matter when separating elements.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\">&#x3C;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span> = [\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Banana\"</span>,\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Apple\"</span>,\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Squash\"</span>\n];\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\">?></span>\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Trailing Comma</h2>\n<p>Does not matter.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Still parses correctly.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\">&#x3C;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span> = [\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Apple\"</span>,\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Banana\"</span>,\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Squash\"</span>,\n];\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\">?></span>\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Array Keys</h2>\n<p>Indexed arrays have indexes as keys by default.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Associative arrays have names as keys.</li>\n</ul>\n<pre><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\">&#x3C;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span> = [\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Apple\"</span> => <span class=\"hljs-number\">12</span>,\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Banana\"</span> => <span class=\"hljs-number\">10</span>,\n    <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Tomato\"</span> => <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"Tasty\"</span>\n];\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\">?></span>\n</code></pre>\n<h2>Declare Empty Array</h2>\n<p>You can declare an empty array and add items later.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\">&#x3C;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span> = [];\n<span class=\"hljs-comment\">// Try adding items</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\">?></span>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Same with associative arrays.</p>\n<h2>Mixing Array Keys</h2>\n<p>You can have arrays with both indexed and named keys.</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"hljs-meta\">&#x3C;?php</span>\n\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span> = [];\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span>[<span class=\"hljs-number\">0</span>] = <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"apples\"</span>;\n<span class=\"hljs-variable\">$foods</span>[<span class=\"hljs-string\">\"fruit\"</span>] = <span class=\"hljs-string\">\"cherries\"</span>;\n\n<span class=\"hljs-meta\">?></span>\n</code></pre>",
